\
These are pretty typical utility classes you find in most stylesheets. We could set this up as a mixin, passing in a bunch of values to determine how the class should be written. However, what if we did something different instead? Let\'92s write a statement that says if the float property is set to left, then set the margin one way. We can write a corresponding statement for the right property.\
